Fresh Pi session: CODE AND CANON TDD REVIEW.

Inputs:
- Prompt, approved use case, test-list history, TDD reports, and regression report: {{run.dir}}
- Worktree: {{run.worktree-dir}}
- Base branch: {{inputs.base-branch}}

Goal:
Review the accepted behavior, implementation, tests, and Canon TDD evidence and explicitly pass or fail.

Rules:
- Do not edit source code, tests, commits, push, or create a PR.
- Review the diff against the base branch.
- Check correctness, regressions, security, maintainability, and focused scope.
- Confirm every completed scenario has a meaningful concrete test, no pending scenarios remain, assertions were not weakened, discoveries were not silently dropped, and refactoring did not introduce behavior.
- Confirm the implementation satisfies the use case without speculative extra scope.
- Produce only concrete actionable findings. On failure, write issues for repair.

Write:
- Report: {{run.dir}}/review/report-{{run.round}}.md
- Status: {{run.dir}}/review/status-{{run.round}}.json
- On failure: {{run.dir}}/review/issues-{{run.round}}.json

Status examples:
{"status":"pass","summary":"code and Canon TDD review passed","issues_file":null}
{"status":"fail","summary":"review found issues","issues_file":"review/issues-{{run.round}}.json"}
